Class Alive

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.unipr.sowide.actodes.actor.Behavior
      • it.unipr.sowide.actosis.automata.Cell<java.lang.String>
        • it.unipr.sowide.actosis.examples.gol.Alive
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public final class Alive
extends Cell<java.lang.String>
    The Alive class defines a behavior identifying the alive state of a cell of the game of life. During the simulation this behavior processes the messages coming from the alive neighbors until their number allows it to remain in the alive state. Default minimal and maximal values for remaining in the alive state are 2 and 3. These values can be modifies through the use of configuration properties.
